Introduced Version
SENATE BILL No. 200
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 20-26.
Synopsis: Public school matters. Provides that choice of law and
certain indemnity provisions contained in contracts entered into,
amended, or renewed after June 30, 2026, between a school and a
vendor are against public policy and are void and unenforceable.
Provides that a public school, including a charter school, that refuses
to allow certain organizations to provide information to students on
school property are subject to a reduction of state tuition support.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Raatz
January 6, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Education and Career
Development.
